Event.info: OSINT - The Curious Case of Notepad and Chthonic: Exposing a Malicious Infrastructure

Attribute.value:
Recently, Iâ€™ve been investigating malware utilizing PowerShell and have spent a considerable amount of time refining ways to identify new variants of attacks as they appear. This posting is a follow-up of my previous work on this subject in  â€œPulling Back the Curtains on EncodedCommand PowerShell Attacksâ€.

In a sample I recently analyzed, something stood out as extremely suspicious which led me down a rabbit hole, uncovering malicious infrastructure supporting Chthonic, Nymaim, and other malware and malicious websites.

Throughout this blog post I present my analysis and thought process during this research, but if you would just like a list of the findings, they are over on our Unit42 GitHub.
